thesis.description: Framed by the sociocritical concept of incipit that sets forth the conditions of readability and the narrative contract, our hermeneutics applies a theoretical and methodological praxis to three fictive texts. To determine readability as mediation of the social discourse, the application of an intertextual reading has been undertaken. Focusing specifically on the feminist discourse, our critical point of view foregrounds those elements that deconstruct the patriarch as positive value.
